div1.p:
Mr.Justice Vaughan thus depos'd. Several of the Shoplifters were brought before me to be examin'd. Holms would fain have been an Evidence, and named I believe near 40 Robberies, that she had been concern'd in, but she having been transported, I could not admit her. Then Turner offer'd to become an Evidence, and confest that she had committed several Felonies in Company with Fitzpatrick. I asked her if she had ever been in Newgate. No, says she, but I was one Night indeed a walking in Fleet-street with a Girl (
Molly Grainge
) and a Gentleman pick'd us up, and carried us to the Tavern, and she pick'd his Pocket, and was hang'd for it. At last Mary Burton came in a voluntary Evidence, and the Information that she then gave me, agrees in every particular with what she now swears in Court.
